  "assertion": {
    "title": "Adding transcendental & square operators with tuned search budget improves GP symbolic regression",
    "kind": "result",
    "statement": "Adding sin, cos, exp, log, sqrt, and square unary operators to GP symbolic regression increases exact matches from 18/50 to 20/50 and mean R\u00b2 from 0.438 to 0.873, but only when the search budget (population size, generations, elitism) is increased to compensate for the larger operator search space. Without increased search budget, exact matches drop to 13/50 despite mean R\u00b2 improving to 0.818, because the GP wastes search effort exploring transcendental paths for algebraic equations.",
    "claim": "supported"
  },
